data.text: Hi @jasmine_learna  I like to let it grow a bit more, it goes taller and bushier, and just before it start to flower I harvest the stalk (with gloves), peel it and eat it fresh, it's super juicy and taste a little like celery, only with many more vitamins and minerals.
